 Atkinson, Ass. Director of Estates, who suggested Lauren was the person I needed to speak to. An email was sent to Lauren last week regarding George''s referral, and Lauren responded this afternoon. Lauren has copied in her colleague, Stuart, Sustainability Manager, confirming that both were happy to schedule a consultation. Lauren and Stuart both report directly into George. I followed up by phone to book the consultation directly. Lauren confirmed the air quality piece crosses between her transport remit and Stuart''s sustainability remit. Current monitoring is basic - diffusion tubes purchased independently, put up for a few weeks and sent to a lab, done roughly twice yearly when it should ideally be quarterly. No real-time visibility, no source attribution, entirely retrospective. The trust is signed up to the NHS Clean Air Framework and the Green Plan contains specific air quality targets. Lauren offered to send over the Green Plan link and Clean Air\nFramework ahead of the consultation to help frame it. No objections raised. Consultation booked for Wednesday 20th May at 10am with both Lauren and Stuart attending. James to be briefed that current monitoring is diffusion tubes twice yearly - the gap between that and continuous real-time monitoring with source attribution is the central framing for the consultation.","(Primary) 1. Contact First Name":"George","(Primary) 1. Contact  Last Name":"Atkinson","(Primary) 1. Contact Title":"Associate Director Of Estates","(Primary) 1. Personal LinkedIn":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/george-atkinson-bb32a789","(Primary) 1. Direct Dial - Mobile":"+44 7770 970800","(Primary) 1. Direct Email - Work":"george.atkinson@uhd.nhs.uk","2. Contact Firstname":"Bernard Bhukal","2. Contact Lastname":"BEng","2. Contact Title":"Associate Director Of Operational Estates","2. Personal LinkedIn":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/bernard-bhukal-beng-miet-b0290513","2. Direct Email - Work":"bernard.bhukal@uhd.nhs.uk","3. Contact First Name":"Berna